SOP: Pump Cavitation and Seal Leakage

1. Confirm suction pressure, discharge pressure, vibration, flow, and seal leakage rate.
2. If pressure is critically low, reduce pump speed or switch to standby pump.
3. Inspect suction strainer, suction valve position, air ingress, and NPSH margin.
4. Lock out pump before opening suction or seal chamber components.
5. Replace mechanical seal if face wear, scoring, or thermal damage is confirmed.
6. Flush pump casing and verify clean water or hydraulic fluid before restart.
7. Restart gradually and verify stable pressure and reduced vibration.
